2. Iterate through the graph edges (red and blue) and update the color of adjacent nodes if they have the same color.
3. Initialize result array with 0 for all nodes.
4. Iterate through the graph edges again and update the result array with the count of alternating colors encountered.
5. Return the result array.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because we iterate through the graph edges once and then again for each node. The space complexity is O(n) due to storing the result array and color array. The energy implications are low as the algorithm only involves simple arithmetic operations and does not consume significant energy.

